  "text": "Parallel Discrete Event Simulation (PDES) techniques are well known for being a classical means to develop simulation systems featuring high performance, which is essential for differentiated contexts, such as symbiotic systems or simulationbased (time-critical) decision making. The basic idea underlying these techniques is to partition the simulation model into several distinct objects, also known as Logical Processes (LPs) [CITATION_1] , which concurrently execute simulation events on clusters, SMP/multi-core machines and/or even desktop grids [CITATION_2] .",
